class Solution {
    public int reverseBits(int n) {
        int result=0;
        for(int i=0;i<32;i++)
        
        {
            result <<=1;
            result |=(n&1);
            n>>=1;
        }
        return result;
    }
}



ğŸ§  What These 3 Lines Really Do

Every loop:

Make space in result (shift left)

Take last bit of n

Put that bit into result

Remove that bit from n
